\begin_layout Theorem
\begin_inset Argument 1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Jensen's inequality
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "thm:jensenInequality"

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\measurespace$
\end_inset

 be a measure space wth 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\left(\X\right)=1.$
\end_inset

 For any integrable function 
\begin_inset Formula $f\in\Lp1{\mu}$
\end_inset

 and a convex function 
\begin_inset Formula $g:\R\to\R$
\end_inset

, we have that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lebInt{\mu}{g\circ f}\geq g\left(\lebInt{\mu}f\right).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
First note that for any restriction of 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 to any interval 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[-n,n\right],$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 has supporting lines everywhere on 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(-n,n\right)$
\end_inset

 by Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:convexSupportingLines"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

can be arbitrarily large, 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 admits a supporting line at 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{0}=\lebInt{\mu}f.$
\end_inset

That is to say, there exists an affine function 
\begin_inset Formula $l$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
l\left(\lebInt{\mu}f\right)=g\left(\lebInt{\mu}f\right)
\]

\end_inset

and
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
l\left(f\left(x\right)\right)\leq g\left(f\left(x\right)\right)
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\R$
\end_inset

.
 Any affine function 
\begin_inset Formula $l:\R\to\R$
\end_inset

